
@startuml

' Define classes
class Resident {
  +name: String
  +streetAddress: String
  +phoneNumber: String
  +email: String (optional)
  +descriptionOfItems: String
  +schedulePickup(date: Date, time: Time)
}

class Item {
  +itemID: String
  +description: String
  +dimensions: Dimensions
  +weight: Weight
  +category: Category
}

class PickupRequest {
  +requestID: String
  +resident: Resident
  +pickupDate: Date
  +pickupTime: Time
  +items: List<Item>
}

class Vehicle {
  +vehicleID: String
  +storageCapacity: Capacity
  +driver: VolunteerDriver (optional)
}

class VolunteerDriver {
  +driverID: String
  +name: String
  +availableDays: List<Date>
  +assignToVehicle(vehicle: Vehicle)
}

class PickupRoute {
  +routeID: String
  +vehicle: Vehicle
  +pickupRequests: List<PickupRequest>
  +scheduleRoute()
}

class DistributionCenter {
  +processItems(items: List<Item>)
  +tagItem(item: Item)
  +correctDescription(item: Item)
  +assignCategory(item: Item)
}

class FoodBank {
  +receiveNonPerishableFoods(items: List<Item>)
}

class Client {
  +clientID: String
  +name: String
  +address: String
  +preferredCategories: List<Category>
}

class ArticleDelivery {
  +deliveryID: String
  +client: Client
  +item: Item
  +deliveryTime: Time
  +arrangeDelivery()
}

class NotificationService {
  +notifyClient(client: Client, items: List<Item>)
}

' Associations

Resident --> PickupRequest
PickupRequest --> Item
PickupRequest --> PickupRoute
Vehicle --> PickupRoute
VolunteerDriver --> Vehicle
PickupRoute --> PickupRequest
DistributionCenter --> Item
FoodBank --> Item
Client --> ArticleDelivery
ArticleDelivery --> Item
NotificationService --> Client
NotificationService --> ArticleDelivery

@enduml

---

### ✅ Explanation of Key Entities and Relationships:

- **Resident**: The person who schedules a pickup.
- **Item**: Represents the item being picked up. Includes description, dimensions, weight, and category.
- **PickupRequest**: A request made by a resident to schedule a pickup.
- **Vehicle**: A pickup vehicle with storage capacity and a driver.
- **VolunteerDriver**: A person who can drive a vehicle on certain days.
- **PickupRoute**: A route planned for a vehicle on a specific day.
- **DistributionCenter**: Processes items received from pickups, tags them, and assigns categories.
- **FoodBank**: Receives non-perishable food items directly from pickups.
- **Client**: A recipient of articles from H2S, possibly requiring delivery.
- **ArticleDelivery**: A delivery of an item to a client.
- **NotificationService**: Sends notifications to clients about available items.

